NHS 24 STAFF in Glasgow have been recognised for their dedication and commitment at an awards ceremony. NHS call staff rewarded for dedication NHS 24 STAFF in Glasgow have been recognised for their dedication and commitment at an awards ceremony.Among them was Tony McLaren, National Coordinator for Breathing Space, who undertook a 600-mile cycle across Scotland to raise awareness of mental health issues.The 54-year-old was one of five members of staff from NHS 24's Cardonald contact centre to win awards. 